    "Faure was trained as a surgeon and spent his early years as a medical doctor, serving as a medical officer in the First World War.": [],
    "He received his first job in the art world from the writer \u00c9mile Zola (1840-1902) who secured Faure's appointment as editor of <em>L'Aurore</em>, the paper in which Zola published his article \"J'Accuse\".": [],
    "Faure's 1904 pamphlet on Velasquez led him to establish an adult school in 1905, where he delivered a series of lectures entitled <em>L'Histoire de l'art</em>.": [],
    "This series was later compiled into five volumes, published in 1920-1921.": [],
